Sentencas: A mathematical model to calculate the volume specific three-phase boundary length in the porous composite electrodes of solid-oxide fuel cell is presented.
Titulo: Three-phase boundary length in solid-oxide fuel cells: A mathematical model

Sentencas: The model is exclusively based on geometrical considerations accounting for porosity, particle diameter, particle size distribution, and solids phase distribution.
Titulo: Three-phase boundary length in solid-oxide fuel cells: A mathematical model

Sentencas: Results are presented for uniform particle size distribution as well as for non-uniform particle size distribution.
Titulo: Three-phase boundary length in solid-oxide fuel cells: A mathematical model
